-- New Zealand's June House Price Index Rises 0.6% From the Previous Month
-- Tracy Withers
-- 2010-07-13T22:05:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/new-zealand-s-june-house-price-index-rises-0-6-from-the-previous-month.html

          
          
             New Zealand house prices rose 0.6
percent in June from May, according to an index published by the
Real Estate Institute of New Zealand Inc.  
 The number of properties sold fell to 4,575 from 5,206
in May, the Auckland-based institute said in an e-mailed
statement. From a year ago, sales fell 24 percent.  
 The median time to sell a house rose to 45 days from 43
days in May, and from 41 days in June last year.  
          
          


  


        